Garage transformation tutorial ‚ú®
Step by step instructions;

Here‚Äôs how we transformed this old concrete garage into a chic Scandi Inspired building.

1) Remove old Wooden panelling from the front.
2) Adjust the wooden frame to suit the panels (ours wasn‚Äôt straight, so we straightened this up.
3) Pre drill Holes through the concrete and Screw the 2x1 slats from the inside of the garage.
4) Attach corner piece to the side and front.
5) Cut Panels to size, they simply hook on to each other, and then you screw the opposite side. Continue the the end. 
6) Add either another corner piece or J piece to finish.
7) On the the front. The corner pieces were on the outside of the walls. We then lined around the Door with the J pieces.
8) we then cut the panels to pop them i between the corner and J piece and continued over the top.
9) for the roof we had a J piece at one end and the other side was against the fascia board. We repeated the same process as the side but with out the corner panels. 

It‚Äôs that easy, any questions? Just ask!

Replying to @Paloma Cambron When I was making over our garage, I knew the floors needed some love. I did some research and found this concrete and garage 1-part epoxy coating paint at Home Depot. It works great! I got it in the color Smoked Tan. 

To prep the floors
1. I cleared out the garage
2. I pressured washed the floors and made sure it was clear of any debris/dirt.
3. Once it dried, I brushed on the paint around the perimeter. 
4. I rolled the paint on to the entire garage floor and let it fully dried before applying the second coat. 
5. As per the instructions, I let it cure for 7 days before I parked my car on it. 

It has been about 5 months now.  There are a few tiny scuff marks  but nothing noticeable. We park our cars on it daily.
